1
00:00:34,388 --> 00:00:39,360
(Fishing boat mooring point)

2
00:00:45,079 --> 00:00:46,960
Lin Zhiyang, wait for me.

3
00:00:48,240 --> 00:00:49,840
Don't run so fast.

4
00:00:50,439 --> 00:00:51,679
You can't catch up with me.

5
00:00:52,560 --> 00:00:53,719
Kids, stop it.

6
00:00:55,475 --> 00:00:59,008
(Year 1994)

7
00:01:00,679 --> 00:01:01,640
Take a look.

8
00:01:01,840 --> 00:01:03,039
Big fish today.

9
00:01:03,119 --> 00:01:04,200
Take a look.

10
00:01:05,920 --> 00:01:07,079
Madam, I'll take this one.

11
00:01:07,079 --> 00:01:07,879
The mackerel?

12
00:01:12,239 --> 00:01:12,959
Is it pretty?

13
00:01:12,959 --> 00:01:13,760
Yeah.

14
00:01:14,000 --> 00:01:15,232
- Here.
- Thank you, Zhitao.

15
00:01:15,840 --> 00:01:17,040
It's so pretty.

16
00:01:20,439 --> 00:01:21,159
How heavy is it?

17
00:01:21,159 --> 00:01:22,719
Two jin and eight liang.

18
00:01:38,599 --> 00:01:39,319
The two of you.

19
00:01:39,719 --> 00:01:40,480
Unload the goods.

20
00:01:40,840 --> 00:01:41,879
Hurry up.

21
00:01:42,680 --> 00:01:44,200
I'm telling you to hurry up.

22
00:01:58,439 --> 00:01:59,680
You can't even buy a drink?

23
00:02:00,120 --> 00:02:01,519
Why did you get the wrong drink?

24
00:02:01,519 --> 00:02:02,599
Hide. Hurry up.

25
00:02:02,760 --> 00:02:04,079
Why did you get the wrong drink?

26
00:02:05,719 --> 00:02:06,239
Get lost.

27
00:02:06,239 --> 00:02:07,560
Mom!

28
00:02:07,560 --> 00:02:09,319
Go away!

29
00:02:26,100 --> 00:02:28,322
(Deep condolences
May her noble soul rest in peace)

30
00:02:29,199 --> 00:02:30,960
She's an official now.
Why would she come?

31
00:02:32,759 --> 00:02:34,759
It's all because of what her dad did.

32
00:02:35,599 --> 00:02:36,520
Uncle, Auntie.

33
00:02:36,719 --> 00:02:38,360
Look who came to her mom's funeral.

34
00:02:40,319 --> 00:02:42,360
Do you still consider yourself a Lin?

35
00:02:43,560 --> 00:02:44,400
All these years...

36
00:02:44,479 --> 00:02:45,719
Enough, forget it.

37
00:03:01,400 --> 00:03:02,639
Change into mourning clothes.

38
00:03:02,960 --> 00:03:03,919
Stay in mourning.

39
00:03:04,879 --> 00:03:06,719
I have work to do. I'm leaving.

40
00:03:07,240 --> 00:03:07,960
How can you...

41
00:03:08,240 --> 00:03:08,919
What's with her?

42
00:03:08,919 --> 00:03:10,080
Then why did you come back?

43
00:03:10,800 --> 00:03:11,800
What is she doing?

44
00:03:15,120 --> 00:03:16,120
Are you really that busy?

45
00:03:29,439 --> 00:03:30,960
Dad, stop it.

46
00:03:31,080 --> 00:03:32,719
Dad, stop.

47
00:03:36,120 --> 00:03:37,919
Dad, stop it.

48
00:03:37,919 --> 00:03:39,280
A pig is smarter than you.

49
00:03:40,479 --> 00:03:41,599
Dad, stop.

50
00:03:41,599 --> 00:03:42,639
You're protecting her?

51
00:03:42,879 --> 00:03:44,159
- I'm providing for you.
- Stop!

52
00:03:44,400 --> 00:03:45,439
Stop it.

53
00:03:45,919 --> 00:03:46,840
You're protecting her?

54
00:04:16,319 --> 00:04:17,279
You've grown so tall.

55
00:04:26,720 --> 00:04:27,560
Keep it.

56
00:05:48,180 --> 00:06:01,216
=Endless Protection=

57
00:06:01,952 --> 00:06:04,805
=Episode 3=

58
00:06:09,160 --> 00:06:10,439
Come with me. We need to talk.

59
00:06:10,439 --> 00:06:11,104
Okay.

60
00:06:12,959 --> 00:06:13,759
Bad news.

61
00:06:14,600 --> 00:06:15,399
Take a look.

62
00:06:16,224 --> 00:06:17,759
(This is a real-name report...)

63
00:06:18,080 --> 00:06:19,319
This video is everywhere

64
00:06:19,560 --> 00:06:21,240
on Weibo, BBS, and Tieba.

65
00:06:21,399 --> 00:06:24,279
(Lin Zhitao bent the law
to shield criminals.)

66
00:06:24,279 --> 00:06:25,120
What does she want?

67
00:06:25,120 --> 00:06:25,839
Lin.

68
00:06:26,920 --> 00:06:28,279
The inspectors are here.

69
00:06:29,439 --> 00:06:30,279
Prosecutor Lin.

70
00:06:30,560 --> 00:06:32,240
The victim's family

71
00:06:32,240 --> 00:06:33,120
of "4.24 homicide"

72
00:06:33,480 --> 00:06:34,639
has submitted a request

73
00:06:34,639 --> 00:06:36,600
to investigate your conduct.

74
00:06:37,439 --> 00:06:38,480
Please cooperate.

75
00:06:42,624 --> 00:06:43,439
Okay.

76
00:06:44,240 --> 00:06:45,839
In the prosecutorial work,

77
00:06:46,319 --> 00:06:47,360
did Prosecutor Lin Zhitao

78
00:06:47,360 --> 00:06:49,279
violate procedural regulations

79
00:06:49,680 --> 00:06:52,279
by privately meeting with
the defendant's family or lawyer?

80
00:06:52,759 --> 00:06:53,680
No, she didn't.

81
00:06:53,879 --> 00:06:56,040
Prosecutor Lin prioritizes
procedural justice.

82
00:06:56,720 --> 00:06:57,399
Officer Liu.

83
00:06:57,839 --> 00:06:59,959
While handling the evidence,

84
00:07:00,360 --> 00:07:01,639
did Prosecutor Lin Zhitao

85
00:07:01,639 --> 00:07:03,720
show any bias
in the organization and adoption

86
00:07:03,720 --> 00:07:04,680
of evidence?

87
00:07:05,000 --> 00:07:05,839
Prosecutor Lin

88
00:07:05,839 --> 00:07:07,439
confirmed all the evidence with us

89
00:07:07,439 --> 00:07:08,319
multiple times

90
00:07:08,319 --> 00:07:09,240
and righteously applied

91
00:07:09,240 --> 00:07:10,680
for supplementary investigation,

92
00:07:10,680 --> 00:07:12,120
strictly following the regulations.

93
00:07:12,319 --> 00:07:13,639
Did she show different attitudes

94
00:07:13,879 --> 00:07:15,680
towards the defendant's family

95
00:07:15,759 --> 00:07:16,959
and the victim's family?

96
00:07:17,199 --> 00:07:19,360
Did she make any improper promises?

97
00:07:20,079 --> 00:07:21,399
She upholds justice

98
00:07:21,759 --> 00:07:23,399
and is serious about her work.

99
00:07:23,920 --> 00:07:25,319
She works overtime every day,

100
00:07:25,600 --> 00:07:26,600
staying up all night.

101
00:07:27,160 --> 00:07:28,160
The records show that

102
00:07:28,439 --> 00:07:29,600
Prosecutor Lin applied for

103
00:07:29,600 --> 00:07:31,279
an investigation into the backgrounds

104
00:07:31,399 --> 00:07:34,120
and economic conditions
of the three suspects.

105
00:07:35,519 --> 00:07:36,240
What's wrong?

106
00:07:36,639 --> 00:07:39,160
She needs to know the suspects' motives.

107
00:07:39,319 --> 00:07:40,279
This is common.

108
00:07:40,279 --> 00:07:41,279
When we work on cases...

109
00:07:41,279 --> 00:07:42,199
Next question.

110
00:07:44,279 --> 00:07:45,240
Do you know

111
00:07:45,240 --> 00:07:46,240
the relationship between

112
00:07:46,240 --> 00:07:48,439
Prosecutor Lin Zhitao
and the defense attorney?

113
00:07:48,759 --> 00:07:49,439
Prosecutor Lin's

114
00:07:49,439 --> 00:07:51,160
relationship with the defense attorney

115
00:07:51,160 --> 00:07:52,240
doesn't call for recusal.

116
00:07:52,920 --> 00:07:53,920
Please address the issue

117
00:07:53,920 --> 00:07:55,920
of accepting money
from the defense attorney.

118
00:08:02,720 --> 00:08:03,519
I didn't take it.

119
00:08:03,892 --> 00:08:05,560
(Who are you?)

120
00:08:05,560 --> 00:08:06,439
Back then,

121
00:08:06,439 --> 00:08:08,600
my buddies and I were ready to go home.

122
00:08:08,720 --> 00:08:10,120
A young buddy came over, crying.

123
00:08:10,120 --> 00:08:11,879
He said he was robbed.

124
00:08:11,879 --> 00:08:12,920
I asked, "Who robbed you?"

125
00:08:13,639 --> 00:08:15,199
At first, he wouldn't say.

126
00:08:15,759 --> 00:08:16,600
I got mad at him.

127
00:08:16,600 --> 00:08:17,439
Then he said

128
00:08:18,199 --> 00:08:20,279
that he was robbed
by a few thugs bigger than us.

129
00:08:20,480 --> 00:08:21,759
And they beat him up.

130
00:08:22,360 --> 00:08:24,079
I got so angry when I heard that.

131
00:08:24,399 --> 00:08:25,759
They messed with my buddy?

132
00:08:26,040 --> 00:08:27,040
Can I tolerate that?

133
00:08:27,240 --> 00:08:28,560
I gave the order

134
00:08:29,439 --> 00:08:31,120
and all my buddies stood up.

135
00:08:31,120 --> 00:08:31,800
They ran away?

136
00:08:31,959 --> 00:08:32,919
Shut up.

137
00:08:33,919 --> 00:08:35,200
Then what?

138
00:08:35,200 --> 00:08:36,360
D-Did you win the fight?

139
00:08:36,360 --> 00:08:37,440
"Win the fight"?

140
00:08:38,039 --> 00:08:40,360
We scared them silly when we appeared.

141
00:08:40,519 --> 00:08:41,919
Someone as big as you

142
00:08:41,919 --> 00:08:43,480
even peed his pants.

143
00:08:43,879 --> 00:08:45,399
He just gave us the money back.

144
00:08:46,080 --> 00:08:47,840
Instructor Bai, are you bluffing?

145
00:08:48,279 --> 00:08:50,159
Yunhai Seven Heroes.

146
00:08:50,559 --> 00:08:51,519
Haven't you heard?

147
00:08:52,000 --> 00:08:52,759
I'm the Boss.

148
00:08:52,759 --> 00:08:53,759
No, I haven't.

149
00:08:53,879 --> 00:08:56,840
Yunhai Seven Heroes,
chivalrous and courageous.

150
00:08:56,840 --> 00:08:58,840
Dominating Nanwan
with unmatched credibility.

151
00:08:58,840 --> 00:09:01,679
Roaming Tapo and unifying Chanquan.

152
00:09:02,240 --> 00:09:03,320
Yunhai

153
00:09:04,519 --> 00:09:05,440
is my turf.

154
00:09:05,600 --> 00:09:06,720
I haven't heard of that.

155
00:09:07,200 --> 00:09:09,720
And this name is so lame.

156
00:09:12,159 --> 00:09:14,200
You little rascals
wouldn't know my name.

157
00:09:15,279 --> 00:09:17,159
Can we join your gang once we're out?

158
00:09:17,360 --> 00:09:18,200
My "gang"?

159
00:09:19,720 --> 00:09:20,879
Even I have quit that life

160
00:09:20,879 --> 00:09:21,919
as the gang leader.

161
00:09:21,919 --> 00:09:22,679
Are you serious?

162
00:09:22,960 --> 00:09:23,960
Clean the wards tomorrow.

163
00:09:26,440 --> 00:09:27,720
A real boss

164
00:09:27,720 --> 00:09:29,559
will only tell you to follow the law.

165
00:09:29,879 --> 00:09:31,679
Those who incite you to commit crimes

166
00:09:31,679 --> 00:09:33,799
are actually big fools.

167
00:09:35,399 --> 00:09:36,080
Got it?

168
00:09:36,080 --> 00:09:37,039
Got it.

169
00:09:39,039 --> 00:09:39,919
It's about time.

170
00:09:43,279 --> 00:09:44,039
Attention!

171
00:09:46,016 --> 00:09:46,639
Take them away.

172
00:09:46,919 --> 00:09:48,080
Turn right.

173
00:09:49,519 --> 00:09:51,360
First squad, march forward.

174
00:09:52,159 --> 00:09:52,879
Second squad, go.

175
00:09:55,039 --> 00:09:55,679
Bro.

176
00:09:55,879 --> 00:09:57,440
Can you tell a new story next time?

177
00:09:57,440 --> 00:09:59,320
I've heard this story
no less than 50 times.

178
00:09:59,399 --> 00:10:00,679
This is the easiest story

179
00:10:00,799 --> 00:10:01,960
to memorize.

180
00:10:02,519 --> 00:10:03,600
Those rascals grew up

181
00:10:03,600 --> 00:10:04,919
differently from us.

182
00:10:05,480 --> 00:10:06,960
We were watching Black Cat Detective,

183
00:10:07,080 --> 00:10:08,320
which taught us to do good.

184
00:10:08,879 --> 00:10:10,600
They grew up watching
Young and Dangerous,

185
00:10:10,679 --> 00:10:12,039
learning about brotherhood.

186
00:10:12,799 --> 00:10:14,360
If you don't win their respect,

187
00:10:14,440 --> 00:10:15,679
why would they listen

188
00:10:15,759 --> 00:10:16,720
to your lectures?

189
00:10:17,200 --> 00:10:18,399
So this trick is foolproof?

190
00:10:20,320 --> 00:10:22,120
It didn't work with Huang Jiawang.

191
00:10:22,960 --> 00:10:24,120
Your noodles were wasted?

192
00:10:24,480 --> 00:10:25,799
Just as you predicted.

193
00:10:26,919 --> 00:10:28,080
We need to ignore him

194
00:10:28,240 --> 00:10:29,279
a bit longer.

195
00:10:30,480 --> 00:10:32,159
If he's a good kid in nature,

196
00:10:32,159 --> 00:10:33,519
we can help him.

197
00:10:34,320 --> 00:10:35,159
If he's bad,

198
00:10:35,559 --> 00:10:36,720
we have to intimidate him

199
00:10:36,840 --> 00:10:37,799
and make him behave.

200
00:10:39,519 --> 00:10:41,759
You're busy role-playing
as a gang leader and a teacher.

201
00:10:41,919 --> 00:10:43,519
Don't get confused one day.

202
00:10:44,360 --> 00:10:46,200
Haven't you reached Lu Sheng's parents?

203
00:10:46,519 --> 00:10:47,480
His dad wouldn't come.

204
00:10:48,080 --> 00:10:48,840
So who's coming?

205
00:10:49,360 --> 00:10:50,080
Village committee

206
00:10:50,320 --> 00:10:52,279
said they would bring a fellow villager.

207
00:10:53,683 --> 00:10:56,013
(Sincerely repent)

208
00:11:00,480 --> 00:11:01,799
Why are you in a daze?

209
00:11:02,039 --> 00:11:03,279
Reluctant to leave this dump?

210
00:11:04,416 --> 00:11:05,240
No.

211
00:11:06,679 --> 00:11:07,399
Put these on.

212
00:11:10,360 --> 00:11:11,039
Put them on.

213
00:11:11,039 --> 00:11:12,320
Are you going out like this?

214
00:11:14,848 --> 00:11:15,639
Hurry up.

215
00:11:18,559 --> 00:11:19,240
Thank you, sir.

216
00:11:22,159 --> 00:11:23,200
There are no shops nearby.

217
00:11:23,399 --> 00:11:24,519
I don't know if they fit.

218
00:11:27,440 --> 00:11:28,039
Instructor Bai.

219
00:11:28,840 --> 00:11:29,960
Didn't my parents come?

220
00:11:31,720 --> 00:11:32,679
Maybe they're busy.

221
00:11:33,120 --> 00:11:33,879
Get out first.

222
00:11:36,840 --> 00:11:37,519
Wait.

223
00:11:42,559 --> 00:11:45,360
What's this mess?
Plotting a prison break?

224
00:11:47,120 --> 00:11:48,519
They left me their phone numbers.

225
00:11:58,720 --> 00:11:59,440
Instructor Bai.

226
00:11:59,960 --> 00:12:01,080
Be quiet.

227
00:12:08,000 --> 00:12:09,000
Forget all of it.

228
00:12:09,960 --> 00:12:10,919
Never come back.

229
00:12:32,480 --> 00:12:33,840
Remember what you promised me.

230
00:12:35,840 --> 00:12:36,720
Never come back.

231
00:12:38,679 --> 00:12:39,440
Promise.

232
00:13:04,360 --> 00:13:04,919
Thank you.

233
00:13:42,440 --> 00:13:43,600
Take care of yourself.

234
00:13:44,200 --> 00:13:44,879
Behave.

235
00:13:46,840 --> 00:13:47,600
Let me know

236
00:13:48,480 --> 00:13:49,480
if there is anything.

237
00:13:53,440 --> 00:13:54,360
Don't look back.

238
00:13:55,279 --> 00:13:55,879
It's bad luck.

239
00:13:59,968 --> 00:14:00,600
Go ahead.

240
00:14:24,360 --> 00:14:25,159
Officers.

241
00:14:25,159 --> 00:14:25,840
You are...

242
00:14:25,840 --> 00:14:26,639
I am his uncle.

243
00:14:27,679 --> 00:14:28,279
You know him?

244
00:14:29,519 --> 00:14:31,000
I've watched him grow up.

245
00:14:32,080 --> 00:14:32,799
I'm his uncle.

246
00:14:34,840 --> 00:14:35,584
Uncle Xiong.

247
00:14:37,919 --> 00:14:39,919
(Mental Health Guidance Center)
Help him blend in.

248
00:14:43,328 --> 00:14:44,039
Let's go.

249
00:14:44,240 --> 00:14:44,799
Come on.

250
00:14:45,559 --> 00:14:47,159
You want to retire here?

251
00:14:47,519 --> 00:14:48,039
Get lost.

252
00:14:50,639 --> 00:14:51,960
We'll leave you to work.

253
00:14:55,440 --> 00:14:56,200
Don't look back.

254
00:15:03,399 --> 00:15:04,600
Little brat.

255
00:15:06,932 --> 00:15:08,764
(Yuedong Juvenile Correctional Facility)

256
00:15:11,679 --> 00:15:13,759
Your instructor is quite strict, huh?

257
00:15:16,600 --> 00:15:18,240
I got you a new phone.

258
00:15:20,000 --> 00:15:21,120
How are my mom and Ming?

259
00:15:22,159 --> 00:15:23,159
Forgot about your dad?

260
00:15:25,960 --> 00:15:26,720
Let's go home.

261
00:15:28,879 --> 00:15:29,639
Which home?

262
00:15:30,960 --> 00:15:32,320
Which home do you have in mind?

263
00:15:40,559 --> 00:15:41,279
Ms. Chen.

264
00:15:41,759 --> 00:15:42,840
After receiving the report,

265
00:15:42,840 --> 00:15:44,960
we conducted a thorough investigation.

266
00:15:45,399 --> 00:15:46,279
Prosecutor Lin Zhitao

267
00:15:46,279 --> 00:15:48,200
did nothing wrong
in the judicial process.

268
00:15:49,120 --> 00:15:50,519
The sentencing is based on the law.

269
00:15:51,320 --> 00:15:53,399
If you have any doubts about it,

270
00:15:53,759 --> 00:15:54,600
please tell us.

271
00:15:54,600 --> 00:15:55,799
We will explain in detail.

272
00:16:00,840 --> 00:16:02,960
Regarding your complaint
about her work ethics,

273
00:16:03,159 --> 00:16:05,159
we obtained surveillance footage.

274
00:16:05,720 --> 00:16:08,440
The defense attorney
did offer her a gift.

275
00:16:08,559 --> 00:16:11,360
However, Prosecutor Lin
did not accept it.

276
00:16:19,080 --> 00:16:19,879
Ms. Chen,

277
00:16:21,840 --> 00:16:22,759
intentional homicide

278
00:16:22,759 --> 00:16:24,600
does not always
lead to the death penalty

279
00:16:24,600 --> 00:16:26,240
as most people imagine.

280
00:16:26,840 --> 00:16:28,120
We also take into account

281
00:16:28,120 --> 00:16:30,480
the criminal responsibility
borne by the offender.

282
00:16:32,000 --> 00:16:33,759
I am the Deputy Chief Prosecutor.

283
00:16:35,000 --> 00:16:36,879
We take your concerns very seriously.

284
00:16:37,320 --> 00:16:39,320
And I understand how you feel right now.

285
00:16:39,919 --> 00:16:40,720
So I hope you can

286
00:16:40,720 --> 00:16:41,879
communicate with us.

287
00:16:42,559 --> 00:16:44,039
We also hope the public

288
00:16:44,200 --> 00:16:46,159
can learn more about our work.

289
00:16:46,759 --> 00:16:47,440
Really?

290
00:16:48,399 --> 00:16:49,279
Then tell me.

291
00:16:50,320 --> 00:16:52,399
Why are those children
considered children?

292
00:16:53,679 --> 00:16:56,600
Why is it that my child
was not considered a child?

293
00:16:56,639 --> 00:16:59,039
Why should I give them a chance?

294
00:17:02,000 --> 00:17:03,840
Did they ever give my child a chance?

295
00:17:03,840 --> 00:17:05,759
Did they ever give Wenxuan a chance?

296
00:17:07,119 --> 00:17:09,960
Ms. Chen, I am also a mother.

297
00:17:10,240 --> 00:17:11,200
I understand

298
00:17:11,200 --> 00:17:12,039
your feelings.

299
00:17:12,039 --> 00:17:13,400
No, you don't.

300
00:17:13,400 --> 00:17:15,480
But this case was highly controversial

301
00:17:15,480 --> 00:17:16,960
in the first place.

302
00:17:17,240 --> 00:17:19,240
Without Prosecutor Lin's
relentless efforts,

303
00:17:19,319 --> 00:17:20,319
those three defendants

304
00:17:20,319 --> 00:17:22,119
could have been acquitted.

305
00:17:22,119 --> 00:17:23,799
So please believe in us.

306
00:17:24,000 --> 00:17:24,880
Believe in you?

307
00:17:27,079 --> 00:17:28,640
What do you want me to believe?

308
00:17:30,759 --> 00:17:33,200
What else do you want me to believe?

309
00:17:34,319 --> 00:17:36,519
At the beginning, you said

310
00:17:36,519 --> 00:17:38,000
you'd bring them to justice.

311
00:17:38,000 --> 00:17:39,359
I believed you.

312
00:17:40,319 --> 00:17:41,400
In court,

313
00:17:41,680 --> 00:17:43,240
you said it was intentional homicide.

314
00:17:43,240 --> 00:17:45,440
And I believed in you again.

315
00:17:45,720 --> 00:17:46,799
But what happened?

316
00:17:47,319 --> 00:17:48,759
What did I get in the end?

317
00:17:49,319 --> 00:17:51,880
For how many years were they sentenced?

318
00:17:53,920 --> 00:17:55,359
What do you want me to believe?

319
00:17:55,839 --> 00:17:57,440
- Ms. Chen.
- What can I believe in?

320
00:17:57,799 --> 00:17:58,960
Regarding your request, we...

321
00:17:58,960 --> 00:18:00,119
My request?

322
00:18:01,559 --> 00:18:02,559
My request

323
00:18:03,440 --> 00:18:04,920
is to sentence them to death.

324
00:18:05,480 --> 00:18:08,160
A life for a life. That's only fair.

325
00:18:08,240 --> 00:18:09,640
Don't they deserve to die?

326
00:18:09,640 --> 00:18:10,480
Ms. Chen.

327
00:18:10,799 --> 00:18:12,799
This case was delivered
to the city procuratorate

328
00:18:13,039 --> 00:18:14,920
because of its complexity.

329
00:18:14,960 --> 00:18:15,880
Meanwhile, we wanted

330
00:18:15,880 --> 00:18:17,759
to ease your pain as much as possible.

331
00:18:18,000 --> 00:18:18,640
So,

332
00:18:19,759 --> 00:18:21,759
this is where it ends, huh?

333
00:18:23,240 --> 00:18:25,039
There's nothing you can do, huh?

334
00:18:29,079 --> 00:18:30,160
In that case,

335
00:18:32,240 --> 00:18:32,920
fine.

336
00:18:34,440 --> 00:18:35,480
Let them out.

337
00:18:35,960 --> 00:18:37,039
Let them out.

338
00:18:38,519 --> 00:18:39,559
I'll kill them.

339
00:18:40,400 --> 00:18:41,279
Chen Huiwen.

340
00:18:41,279 --> 00:18:42,480
Could you please

341
00:18:43,119 --> 00:18:44,279
calm down?

342
00:18:44,559 --> 00:18:45,160
Okay?

343
00:18:45,240 --> 00:18:46,519
How dare you talk to me?

344
00:18:48,079 --> 00:18:48,960
Lin Zhitao.

345
00:18:49,079 --> 00:18:51,559
It's all because of you.

346
00:18:52,000 --> 00:18:54,680
- Right now...
- I can't take revenge now!

347
00:18:54,680 --> 00:18:56,279
I know how you feel.

348
00:18:56,279 --> 00:18:56,839
Lin Zhitao.

349
00:18:56,839 --> 00:18:57,519
But it's not...

350
00:18:57,519 --> 00:18:59,119
You are the murderer!

351
00:18:59,119 --> 00:19:00,440
Ms. Chen.

352
00:19:00,440 --> 00:19:02,519
You want me to "calm down"?

353
00:19:02,519 --> 00:19:03,200
Chen Huiwen.

354
00:19:04,319 --> 00:19:05,200
Listen up.

355
00:19:06,000 --> 00:19:07,039
We've been tolerating you

356
00:19:07,039 --> 00:19:08,160
not because we did wrong.

357
00:19:08,160 --> 00:19:09,680
We did nothing wrong.

358
00:19:10,279 --> 00:19:11,799
No matter what you say or do,

359
00:19:12,160 --> 00:19:13,119
the law is the law.

360
00:19:13,119 --> 00:19:14,519
It will not change.

361
00:19:14,519 --> 00:19:15,200
Understand?

362
00:19:15,440 --> 00:19:16,359
Do you understand?

363
00:19:18,039 --> 00:19:18,799
Lin Zhitao.

364
00:19:19,920 --> 00:19:21,400
You are the murderer.

365
00:19:24,240 --> 00:19:25,680
Karma will get you.

366
00:19:27,160 --> 00:19:28,079
Chen Huiwen.

367
00:19:29,359 --> 00:19:32,039
You speak from your standpoint.

368
00:19:42,799 --> 00:19:43,799
Just you wait.

369
00:19:46,720 --> 00:19:47,400
Just you wait.

370
00:19:52,680 --> 00:19:53,376
Ms. Chen.

371
00:19:53,759 --> 00:19:54,440
Ms. Chen.

372
00:19:54,759 --> 00:19:55,359
Ms. Chen.

373
00:19:58,079 --> 00:19:59,799
I'm fine.

374
00:20:22,680 --> 00:20:24,640
(We suggest the following sentencing)

375
00:20:24,640 --> 00:20:25,559
(for the defendants.)

376
00:20:25,839 --> 00:20:27,200
(The defendant Huang Jiawang)

377
00:20:27,480 --> 00:20:29,599
(shall have eight years
of fixed-term imprisonment.)

378
00:20:35,680 --> 00:20:37,680
Why not the death penalty?

379
00:20:38,200 --> 00:20:39,759
You promised me.

380
00:20:39,759 --> 00:20:41,640
You promised to help me.

381
00:20:41,640 --> 00:20:42,880
What does your conscience say?

382
00:20:42,880 --> 00:20:44,640
Can you say you did your best?

383
00:20:44,640 --> 00:20:46,200
You are the murderer.

384
00:20:46,279 --> 00:20:48,599
- You...
- You are the murderer.

385
00:20:48,599 --> 00:20:49,119
(Get lost.)

386
00:20:49,119 --> 00:20:50,519
Mom.

387
00:20:51,160 --> 00:20:53,359
- Get lost.
- Dad, stop.

388
00:20:53,720 --> 00:20:54,880
(Jump, and I'll let you go.)

389
00:20:54,880 --> 00:20:55,680
(Jump.)

390
00:21:40,720 --> 00:21:41,440
Mom.

391
00:21:41,716 --> 00:21:43,480
(Award)

392
00:21:43,480 --> 00:21:44,039
Mom.

393
00:21:46,960 --> 00:21:47,559
Mom?

394
00:21:51,440 --> 00:21:52,359
Where is Ming?

395
00:21:58,279 --> 00:21:58,960
Ming.

396
00:21:59,720 --> 00:22:00,519
Ming?

397
00:22:00,759 --> 00:22:01,400
Ming?

398
00:22:04,079 --> 00:22:04,759
Where is Ming?

399
00:22:05,240 --> 00:22:06,119
I'm talking to you.

400
00:22:06,359 --> 00:22:07,440
Where is Lu Ming?

401
00:22:07,839 --> 00:22:09,319
Where is Lu Ming?

402
00:22:09,559 --> 00:22:10,559
Speak.

403
00:22:11,720 --> 00:22:13,119
He went to learn

404
00:22:13,559 --> 00:22:14,688
from Xiong.

405
00:22:14,688 --> 00:22:15,400
You...

406
00:22:18,920 --> 00:22:19,640
Your hands.

407
00:22:20,519 --> 00:22:21,359
Don't flinch.

408
00:22:22,440 --> 00:22:23,920
What if you get caught?

409
00:22:30,880 --> 00:22:31,680
Sheng.

410
00:22:33,119 --> 00:22:33,839
Go to sleep.

411
00:22:42,480 --> 00:22:43,279
You're back.

412
00:22:44,960 --> 00:22:45,799
Good to see you.

413
00:22:47,920 --> 00:22:48,920
Welcome home.

414
00:22:53,039 --> 00:22:55,200
Why didn't you tell me
your mom passed away?

415
00:22:55,319 --> 00:22:56,799
I could have gone with you.

416
00:22:57,920 --> 00:22:58,960
No need. It's fine.

417
00:22:59,880 --> 00:23:00,519
How is it fine?

418
00:23:00,519 --> 00:23:01,680
Look at you.

419
00:23:02,599 --> 00:23:03,960
You're so pale.

420
00:23:04,559 --> 00:23:05,559
Rest for some days.

421
00:23:05,720 --> 00:23:07,240
No need. I'm not tired.

422
00:23:09,079 --> 00:23:10,200
I see some grey hair.

423
00:23:10,480 --> 00:23:11,839
They've been there.

424
00:23:15,279 --> 00:23:16,400
I'm thinking.

425
00:23:19,000 --> 00:23:20,160
I don't know if what I did

426
00:23:20,160 --> 00:23:22,319
truly helped those three kids.

427
00:23:24,200 --> 00:23:25,680
If it really did help them,

428
00:23:26,559 --> 00:23:27,960
I find it hard to accept.

429
00:23:28,079 --> 00:23:29,839
I don't even know who I'm protecting.

430
00:23:33,119 --> 00:23:34,240
What I'm going to tell you

431
00:23:34,240 --> 00:23:35,519
might be even harder to accept.

432
00:23:37,319 --> 00:23:39,079
The Supreme People's Procuratorate

433
00:23:39,079 --> 00:23:40,599
is setting up a separate department

434
00:23:41,440 --> 00:23:42,799
for juvenile delinquency

435
00:23:42,799 --> 00:23:45,519
and its prosecutorial work in two years.

436
00:23:46,640 --> 00:23:48,160
So, the procuratorate has decided

437
00:23:48,400 --> 00:23:49,200
to establish

438
00:23:49,720 --> 00:23:51,960
a pilot department
for juvenile prosecutorial work.

439
00:23:58,559 --> 00:24:00,440
I want to recommend you for the position

440
00:24:00,559 --> 00:24:01,599
of the director.

441
00:24:08,160 --> 00:24:09,319
You guys are mean.

442
00:24:09,319 --> 00:24:11,160
Setting up a department to punish me?

443
00:24:11,160 --> 00:24:12,160
Is it worth it?

444
00:24:13,960 --> 00:24:14,839
Lin Zhitao.

445
00:24:15,319 --> 00:24:17,240
Don't take yourself so seriously.

446
00:24:17,240 --> 00:24:19,319
You're clearly trying to drive me away.

447
00:24:20,440 --> 00:24:21,359
It's a punishment.

448
00:24:21,359 --> 00:24:22,160
Right?

449
00:24:22,480 --> 00:24:24,799
I'm responsible
for Zhang Wenxuan's case.

450
00:24:24,880 --> 00:24:25,759
I didn't expect

451
00:24:25,759 --> 00:24:27,519
that bringing this case

452
00:24:27,880 --> 00:24:29,400
to the city procuratorate resulted in

453
00:24:29,400 --> 00:24:30,720
unrealistic expectations.

454
00:24:30,880 --> 00:24:31,799
But you did

455
00:24:31,799 --> 00:24:33,240
a perfect job as the prosecutor.

456
00:24:33,240 --> 00:24:35,799
From trial to sentencing,
it was flawless.

457
00:24:35,799 --> 00:24:36,640
Don't sweet-talk me.

458
00:24:36,640 --> 00:24:37,599
I'm not stupid.

459
00:24:38,200 --> 00:24:39,720
You're setting up this department

460
00:24:39,720 --> 00:24:41,039
right at this moment.

461
00:24:41,319 --> 00:24:43,240
Inspectors came and investigated me.

462
00:24:43,240 --> 00:24:43,960
People out there

463
00:24:43,960 --> 00:24:45,319
are pointing fingers at me.

464
00:24:45,319 --> 00:24:46,799
You're putting me to take the blame.

465
00:24:46,799 --> 00:24:47,400
Am I right?

466
00:24:47,400 --> 00:24:48,640
- We...
- I'm the scapegoat, no?

467
00:24:48,640 --> 00:24:49,640
"The scapegoat"?

468
00:24:49,640 --> 00:24:50,359
Come closer.

469
00:24:50,359 --> 00:24:51,480
She's driving me away.

470
00:24:51,680 --> 00:24:52,440
Tell everyone...

471
00:24:52,440 --> 00:24:53,359
Are you done?

472
00:24:54,920 --> 00:24:56,680
How could you say something like that?

473
00:24:56,680 --> 00:24:57,279
I won't go.

474
00:24:57,279 --> 00:24:58,200
You have no choice.

475
00:24:59,319 --> 00:25:00,559
You're the "scapegoat"?

476
00:25:01,480 --> 00:25:03,119
Is it your first day as a prosecutor?

477
00:25:03,119 --> 00:25:04,000
Or do you think

478
00:25:04,000 --> 00:25:05,759
that I can't tell right from wrong?

479
00:25:06,279 --> 00:25:07,119
Haven't I dealt with

480
00:25:07,119 --> 00:25:08,880
difficult family members of the victims?

481
00:25:10,440 --> 00:25:12,160
If I just drive our colleagues away,

482
00:25:12,400 --> 00:25:14,279
do you think I can do my job

483
00:25:14,279 --> 00:25:15,240
to this very day?

484
00:25:15,240 --> 00:25:16,440
Then why do you have to

485
00:25:16,440 --> 00:25:17,759
transfer me at this moment?

486
00:25:17,759 --> 00:25:18,480
I told you.

487
00:25:18,480 --> 00:25:19,960
It was just decided.

488
00:25:27,160 --> 00:25:28,119
Let me talk to you

489
00:25:28,119 --> 00:25:29,359
calmly and seriously.

490
00:25:32,519 --> 00:25:33,920
As a prosecutor for major cases,

491
00:25:34,720 --> 00:25:36,079
I think I'm doing a good job.

492
00:25:37,079 --> 00:25:38,640
I haven't let a felony criminal

493
00:25:38,799 --> 00:25:40,599
get away with a penalty, right?

494
00:25:42,039 --> 00:25:43,119
I didn't even blink

495
00:25:43,880 --> 00:25:45,680
when I supervised the death penalty

496
00:25:45,680 --> 00:25:47,279
and saw those inmates twitching.

497
00:25:48,079 --> 00:25:48,640
I believe

498
00:25:48,640 --> 00:25:50,480
that I'm doing what I do best.

499
00:25:51,000 --> 00:25:51,759
I can do it well.

500
00:25:51,759 --> 00:25:53,240
I will do even better in the future.

501
00:25:54,400 --> 00:25:56,200
You have always believed in me.

502
00:25:57,119 --> 00:25:58,839
So why are you transferring me?

503
00:25:58,839 --> 00:26:00,680
Do you think I can manage kids?

504
00:26:01,200 --> 00:26:02,279
You know best

505
00:26:02,279 --> 00:26:03,640
if I can manage kids.

506
00:26:03,640 --> 00:26:04,720
I can't manage them.

507
00:26:05,039 --> 00:26:06,640
It's difficult even to talk to them.

508
00:26:07,839 --> 00:26:09,519
I don't think I would misjudge.

509
00:26:10,960 --> 00:26:13,480
You have to get over this trauma.

510
00:26:13,640 --> 00:26:14,920
Or you will never become

511
00:26:14,920 --> 00:26:16,640
a competent prosecutor.

512
00:26:16,880 --> 00:26:17,640
There is no trauma.

513
00:26:19,759 --> 00:26:20,480
Just tell me.

514
00:26:20,480 --> 00:26:21,640
Are you seeking

515
00:26:22,960 --> 00:26:23,640
my opinion,

516
00:26:23,640 --> 00:26:24,519
or is it decided?

517
00:26:24,759 --> 00:26:25,920
- It's decided.
- Okay.

518
00:26:25,920 --> 00:26:27,960
- Where are you going?
- What's there to say?

519
00:26:31,960 --> 00:26:33,400
You're really leaving?

520
00:26:33,960 --> 00:26:35,319
A top-ten prosecutor in Yuedong,

521
00:26:35,319 --> 00:26:37,240
who's in charge of major crimes

522
00:26:37,240 --> 00:26:38,680
is going to look after kids.

523
00:26:39,240 --> 00:26:40,440
What a pity.

524
00:26:40,680 --> 00:26:41,359
Pity, huh?

525
00:26:41,519 --> 00:26:42,880
I also think it's a pity.

526
00:26:43,440 --> 00:26:44,200
So who is willing

527
00:26:44,200 --> 00:26:45,599
to come with me?

528
00:26:46,880 --> 00:26:48,720
Zhitao, we'll pass.

529
00:27:05,759 --> 00:27:06,759
Where is it?

530
00:27:07,400 --> 00:27:08,279
I don't know.

531
00:27:14,200 --> 00:27:15,079
Is it here?

532
00:27:16,000 --> 00:27:16,519
Yeah.

533
00:27:17,720 --> 00:27:18,799
Isn't this the logistics?

534
00:27:18,880 --> 00:27:19,400
Yeah.

535
00:27:19,400 --> 00:27:21,359
They'll start fixing
the new office next week.

536
00:27:21,359 --> 00:27:23,200
So you'll have to stay here for now.

537
00:27:23,839 --> 00:27:24,960
Here are the keys.

538
00:27:29,920 --> 00:27:31,079
Zhitao.

539
00:27:34,839 --> 00:27:35,640
Oh my God.

540
00:27:38,240 --> 00:27:38,784
This...

541
00:27:39,960 --> 00:27:42,319
T-This is an office?

542
00:27:44,079 --> 00:27:45,240
This is an exile.

543
00:27:48,839 --> 00:27:49,440
Cheng Wei.

544
00:27:51,160 --> 00:27:52,640
(Fortune)
Do you smell something?

545
00:27:54,519 --> 00:27:55,640
Not really.

546
00:27:56,039 --> 00:27:57,960
It's probably coming from the bathroom.

547
00:28:01,920 --> 00:28:02,640
What do they want?

548
00:28:03,799 --> 00:28:04,400
Cheng Wei.

549
00:28:05,240 --> 00:28:06,519
Can you handle this job

550
00:28:06,519 --> 00:28:07,200
alone?

551
00:28:08,759 --> 00:28:09,680
Come on, Zhitao.

552
00:28:09,799 --> 00:28:11,240
I came here because of you.

553
00:28:13,640 --> 00:28:14,279
Cheng Wei.

554
00:28:15,799 --> 00:28:17,319
Here's a task for you.

555
00:28:19,680 --> 00:28:20,880
Assign me some tasks.

556
00:28:20,880 --> 00:28:21,680
Anything will do.

557
00:28:24,000 --> 00:28:25,359
You want me to assign you tasks?

558
00:28:31,559 --> 00:28:34,680
Why don't we go to
the Juvenile Correctional Facility

559
00:28:34,960 --> 00:28:37,079
to see how the three of them are doing?

560
00:28:37,200 --> 00:28:38,279
Do a follow-up.

561
00:28:38,912 --> 00:28:39,559
Okay.

562
00:28:40,839 --> 00:28:42,200
What should we

563
00:28:42,480 --> 00:28:43,279
ask them...

564
00:28:43,279 --> 00:28:44,000
You decide.

565
00:28:49,640 --> 00:28:50,599
Me?

566
00:28:52,799 --> 00:28:54,839
We can ask Huang Jiawang
to draw a picture.

567
00:28:54,920 --> 00:28:55,720
- Great.
- I think...

568
00:28:58,119 --> 00:28:59,680
Zhitao, stop having those oranges.

569
00:28:59,680 --> 00:29:01,000
Someone will find out.

570
00:29:02,559 --> 00:29:03,640
How much can I eat?

571
00:29:04,000 --> 00:29:08,640
♪Come home often♪

572
00:29:09,000 --> 00:29:13,920
♪Even if just to
help your wife wash dishes♪

573
00:29:14,480 --> 00:29:15,680
♪The husband doesn't♪

574
00:29:15,680 --> 00:29:16,240
Bai.

575
00:29:17,480 --> 00:29:18,119
Well...

576
00:29:18,880 --> 00:29:20,720
Are you in charge of Huang Jiawang?

577
00:29:21,920 --> 00:29:23,400
The prosecutors are coming soon.

578
00:29:23,400 --> 00:29:24,119
Greet them.

579
00:29:24,480 --> 00:29:25,240
